vulnerability.name: USN-5722-1
vulnerability.description: It was discovered that nginx incorrectly handled certain memory operations in the ngx_http_mp4_module module. A local attacker could possibly use this issue with a specially crafted mp4 file to cause nginx to crash, stop responding, or access arbitrary memory. (CVE-2022-41741, CVE-2022-41742)

statements.status_notes: Several security issues were fixed in nginx.
